&lt;div&gt;Seeking a technical leader specializing in Adobe Experience Manager and Edge Delivery Services to spearhead digital transformation initiatives for a global clientele. Serving as the lead technical authority, you will oversee the transition of legacy environments toward AEMaaCS and modern EDS frameworks. This hands-on architectural capacity requires a sophisticated integration of CMS proficiency with NextJS/TypeScript and AI-enabled engineering practices. You will be responsible for the architectural integrity of migration efforts, driving pre-sales engagements, and fostering a culture of engineering excellence through mentorship.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WHAT YOU&#39;LL DO&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Spearhead comprehensive architectural transformations from legacy environments to AEMaaCS and Edge Delivery Services. Perform rigorous ecosystem audits, establish strategic roadmaps, and navigate intricate integration complexities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Architect elite, scalable digital platforms ensuring fluid interoperability between the Adobe suite and enterprise third-party systems, including CRM and advanced analytics&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain a hands-on presence in delivering sophisticated codebases across Java and modern TypeScript/NextJS stacks. Drive uncompromising testing methodologies to guarantee stable, zero-regression deployments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Champion the integration of agentic workflows and AI engineering platforms such as Claude or V0 to optimize software delivery cycles and automate technical documentation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead technical solutioning for global pitches, providing expert resource modeling and scope definition. Act as the primary technical authority for executive-level stakeholder engagements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Cultivate a high-performance engineering culture focused on AI-native practices and state-of-the-art architectural patterns within the Adobe Experience Cloud ecosystem&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WHAT YOU&#39;LL NEED&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;8 to 10 years of engineering experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Adobe AEM architect and other related certifications&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Extensive engineering background spanning over eight years, with a concentrated technical authority in Adobe Experience Manager (Sites/Assets) and Edge Delivery Services. We require a dedicated specialist, not a generalist, to lead these complex environments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated success in orchestrating complex migrations from legacy CMS infrastructures toward modern AEMaaCS and EDS frameworks&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain a hands-on presence across the full technical stack, delivering elite code in Java, JavaScript, TypeScript, and NextJS. Capability to navigate from high-level architecture to resolving critical production bottlenecks is essential&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Champion the use of AI engineering platforms such as Claude, Cursor, or V0 within daily software delivery cycles. Proven ability to automate workflows and optimize delivery through agentic tools&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Expertly navigate architectural trade-offs, leading technical discourse on GraphQL mesh layers, cloud-native deployments, and the evolution of headless versus hybrid patterns&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Sophisticated commercial acumen with the ability to translate technical complexities into clear value propositions for executive-level stakeholders during pre-sales and discovery phases&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven experience fostering excellence across distributed global teams and managing senior engagements within enterprise environments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with solutioning &amp;amp; pre-sales engagements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&

&lt;p&gt;Code and Theory is hiring an Associate Director to work at the core of business transformation engagements within our Enterprise Transformation practice. You will conduct organizational diagnostics, redesign workflows and operating models, support technology adoption, and use AI tools to demonstrate value inside real client processes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is not an advisory role. The expectation is direct: you can design the solution and build the proof of concept that shows it working.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Depending on the client engagement, this role may operate in a forward-deployed capacity — embedded inside a client team, working alongside their engineers, product leads, and operators to ship solutions in real time. That is not a separate track or program. It is a mode this work requires, and the expectation is that you are ready for it when the account calls for it.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WHAT YOU&#39;LL DO&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Map current-state workflows end-to-end and diagnose root causes of operational friction — handoff failures, governance gaps, tooling mismatches, incentive misalignment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Redesign processes for target-state operations: leaner workflows, clearer decision rights, human-agent collaboration where AI accelerates throughput&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design operating models: org structure, roles, governance, cross-functional interaction models&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish performance baselines before engagements begin; build the measurement framework that tracks improvement over the engagement — not just at the end&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify value gaps in stalled implementations: diagnose where technology deployment has outpaced business adoption and restore the path to ROI&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build reporting cadences that give clients a clear line from initiative to impact&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build working AI-powered prototypes directly: LLM APIs, platform-native features, no-code and low-code environments; you have shipped something functional&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use prototypes as the primary tool for stakeholder alignment — a working demo inside the client&#39;s actual process is more effective than a roadmap&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Evaluate where AI changes a workflow and where it is a distraction; advise clients accordingly without overselling&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support rollout of new tools and workflows; ensure adoption is grounded in process design and change management, not just deployment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design enablement materials that make new technology stick&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure technology implementations connect to the operating model they are designed to support&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support complex engagement scoping where client needs are ambiguous or span multiple services&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct diagnostic assessments: value capture, implementation readiness, adoption strategy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute reusable frameworks and tools that improve how the practice qualifies and scopes work&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WHAT YOU&#39;LL NEED&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5-10 years in management consulting or equivalent roles at enterprise technology, SaaS, or professional services&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated experience in at least two of: organizational design, operating model transformation, change management, technology enablement, process engineering, or go-to-market execution&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track record of building structured, evidence-based arguments for senior stakeholders&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience on organizational assessments, process redesigns, or large-scale technology rollouts is a strong differentiator&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands-on experience building AI-powered workflows, automations, or prototypes — you have shipped something functional, not just designed it&lt;/li&gt;
