&lt;p&gt;At Code and Theory, we thrive at the intersection of creativity and technology. We build brands through big ideas, bold storytelling, and content that actually moves people. Our teams don&#39;t just execute work. They shape it. Through a culture of invention, we turn ambitious concepts into memorable experiences that resonate across every channel.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Production is the engine that drives creative work forward at Code and Theory. Our producers are equal parts creative partner and operational powerhouse: planning, scoping, pricing, challenging, and innovating to bring structure to the chaos so the best work can thrive. They know how to spot a great concept, push it further, and get it out the door on time and on budget - while keeping clients genuinely excited about what they&#39;re building together.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WHAT YOU’LL DO&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support active client accounts and internal projects alongside Executive Producers, Senior Directors, and the Head of Production&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own internal projects including new business pitches, awards submissions, case study development&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Keep the team organized, assets gathered, and deadlines met&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track timelines, maintain documentation, and keep assets organized across active projects&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own project status updates, keeping the team informed on what&#39;s due, what&#39;s pending, and what&#39;s next&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Attend client and internal meetings, take accurate notes, and distribute clear recaps with decisions and next steps documented&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build your financial instincts by supporting burn reporting and budget documentation on active projects to start connecting how time, effort, and resources relate to scope&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stay curious about what&#39;s changing in technology, emerging channels, and AI-enabled workflows&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Look for smarter ways to work and move fast enough to actually apply them&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Show up for the team, taking things off people&#39;s plates and running with them&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WHAT YOU’LL NEED&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in production, account management, program management, or a related discipline&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A genuine love of content, storytelling, and creative ideas.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Curiosity about how campaigns, video, social, digital, and experiential work gets made and a desire to be part of making it&lt;/li&gt;
